                  <persName id="t18000709-64-person497">
                  JOHN 
                  DIGBY
               <interp inst="t18000709-64-person497" type="surname" value="DIGBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000709-64-person497" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000709-64-person497" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a labouring manservant to Mr. Bates, a <rs id="t18000709-64-viclabel331" type="occupation">carman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000709-64-victim496 t18000709-64-viclabel331"></join>, at Paddington; I saw the prisoner take the property; I unharnessed my horses about an hour before, in the Foundlingfields; I put the harness into one of the vaults, by where we were at work; I saw the prisoner go into the vault, take them out, and put them in a sack, and carry them away; I followed him, and took him in the Duke of Bedford's private road; I asked him what he was going to do with that property, he said it was his own, I collared him, and secured the property; it is Mr. Bates's property, I was at work not five roods from him, behind a clump of bricks, he did not see me. (Produces the property.)</p>
